{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idca6fd200-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1735"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1735"},"text":"§ 1735.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Forfeitures and deposits","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idca6fd201-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1735/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Credit to separate account in Treasury; appropriation and availability","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any moneys received by the United States as a result of the forfeiture of a bond or other security by a resource developer or purchaser or permittee who does not fulfill the requirements of his contract or permit or does not comply with the regulations of the Secretary; or as a result of a compromise or settlement of any claim whether sounding in tort or in contract involving present or potential damage to the public lands shall be credited to a separate account in the Treasury and are hereby authorized to be appropriated and made available, until expended as the Secretary may direct, to cover the cost to the United States of any improvement, protection, or rehabilitation work on those public lands which has been rendered necessary by the action which has led to the forfeiture, compromise, or settlement.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idca6fd202-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1735/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Expenditure of moneys collected administering Oregon and California Railroad and Coos Bay Wagon Road Grant lands","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any moneys collected under this Act in connection with lands administered under the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1937-08-28"},"text":"August 28, 1937","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/50/874"},"text":"50 Stat. 874","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1181a–118"},"text":"43 U.S.C. 1181a–118","children":[],"tail":"1j),"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002145"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002145"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" shall be expended for the benefit of such land only."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idca6fd203-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1735/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Refunds","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"If any portion of a deposit or amount forfeited under this Act is found by the Secretary to be in excess of the cost of doing the work authorized under this Act, the Secretary, upon application or otherwise, may cause a refund of the amount in excess to be made from applicable funds.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idca6fd204-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/579/tIII/s305"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–579, title III, § 305","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2765"},"text":"90 Stat. 2765","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idca6fd205-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idca6fd206-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idca6fd207-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This Act, referred to in subsecs. (b) and (c), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/579"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–579","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2743"},"text":"90 Stat. 2743","children":[],"tail":", known as the Federal Land Policy and Management Act of 1976. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1937-08-28"},"text":"August 28, 1937","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/50/874"},"text":"50 Stat. 874","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1181a–118"},"text":"43 U.S.C. 1181a–118","children":[],"tail":"1j), referred to in subsec. (b), probably means "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1937-08-28/ch876"},"text":"act Aug. 28, 1937, ch. 876","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/50/874"},"text":"50 Stat. 874","children":[],"tail":", which was formerly classified principally to sections 1181a to 1181f of this title prior to editorial reclassification, and is now classified principally to subchapter I (§ 2601 et seq.) of chapter 44 of this title. Section 3 of the Act, former "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1181c"},"text":"section 1181c of this title","children":[],"tail":", was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/579/tVII/s702"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–579, title VII, § 702","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2787"},"text":"90 Stat. 2787","children":[],"tail":". Sections 1181f–1 to 1181f–4 of this title, included within the parenthetical reference to sections 1181a to 1181j, were enacted by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1939-05-24/ch144"},"text":"act May 24, 1939, ch. 144","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/53/753"},"text":"53 Stat. 753","children":[],"tail":", and were editorially reclassified as subchapter II (§ 2621 et seq.) of chapter 44 of this title. Sections 1181g to 1181j of this title, also included within the parenthetical reference to sections 1181a to 1181j, were enacted by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-06-24/ch357"},"text":"act June 24, 1954, ch. 357","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/270"},"text":"68 Stat. 270","children":[],"tail":", and were editorially reclassified as subchapter III (§ 2631 et seq.) of chapter 44 of this title. For complete classification of these Acts to the Code, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idca6fd208-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idca6fd209-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Availability of Funds for Improvement, Protection, or Rehabilitation of Damaged Public Lands","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/134/tI/s101/c/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–134, title I, § 101(c) [title I]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-04-26"},"text":"Apr. 26, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1321-156"},"text":"110 Stat. 1321–156","children":[],"tail":", 1321–158; renumbered title I, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/140/s1/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–140, § 1(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-05-02"},"text":"May 2, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1327"},"text":"110 Stat. 1327","children":[],"tail":", provided in part: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/104/140/s1/a"},"text":"“That notwithstanding any provision to the contrary of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1976-10-21/s305/a"},"text":"section 305(a) of the Act of October 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1735/a"},"text":"43 U.S.C. 1735(a)","children":[],"tail":"), any moneys that have been or will be received pursuant to that section, whether as a result of forfeiture, compromise, or settlement, if not appropriate for refund pursuant to section 305(c) of that Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1735/c"},"text":"43 U.S.C. 1735(c)","children":[],"tail":"), shall be available and may be expended under the authority of this or subsequent appropriations Acts by the Secretary to improve, protect, or rehabilitate any public lands administered through the Bureau of Land Management which have been damaged by the action of a resource developer, purchaser, permittee, or any unauthorized person, without regard to whether all moneys collected from each such forfeiture, compromise, or settlement are used on the exact lands damage to which led to the forfeiture, compromise, or settlement: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided further","children":[],"tail":", That such moneys are in excess of amounts needed to repair damage to the exact land for which collected.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Similar provisions were contained in the following appropriation acts:","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/74/dC/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–74, div. C, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2026-01-23"},"text":"Jan. 23, 2026","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/140/95"},"text":"140 Stat. 95","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/42/dE/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–42, div. E, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2024-03-09"},"text":"Mar. 9, 2024","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/138/220"},"text":"138 Stat. 220","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/328/dG/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–328, div. G, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/4761"},"text":"136 Stat. 4761","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/dG/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, div. G, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-03-15"},"text":"Mar. 15, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/349"},"text":"136 Stat. 349","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/260/dG/tI"},"